title: Ask HN: Why didn't the Amiga discourage multitasking to reduce system crashes?
text:
The Amiga didn't have process protection and multitasking made it highly unreliable.

Maybe the Amiga could have been a more serious contender in business if it didn't crash all the time due to multitasking?

Ask HN: How to recognize a good startup investor?
text:
1. Does the investor have a good track record?

2. Does the investor have a deep understanding of the startup's industry and market?

3. Does the investor have a network of resources and contacts that can help the startup grow?

4. Does the investor have a history of providing valuable feedback and guidance to startups?

5. Does the investor have a willingness to take a risk on a new company?

Do you agree and What else?
